&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced, high-energy Field Marketing Manager to join the Field Marketing team in North America. The primary responsibility for this role will be executing events and targeted ABM programs across the US regions and helping the Field Marketing team to generate engagement and leads within our target accounts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to leverage your expertise to manage and execute the event and ABM program in order to maximize the return on the investments made. This role is crucial as it directly impacts the company&#39;s ability to connect with target audiences, generate leads, and drive sales through well-executed events and targeted programs. You will get to work on a variety of events from large sponsored third party events, small roundtables, to seminars. We are continually aiming to evolve and improve the events we run, and your feedback will be vital to the continued development of the program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To be eligible for this role, you must be based in the NYC area, and will be expected to go into the office on Mondays, Tuesdays &amp;amp; Thursdays.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Will&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute and shape the regional event and ABM program, partnering with Field Marketing and the broader GTM team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan, coordinate and execute regional events such as 3rd party conferences, in-person happy hours, roadshows and roundtables often with Partners (ISVs, IBM and Global Providers).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage event logistics including (but not limited to) venue selection, swag, prize draws and promotional materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the design team to develop compelling event collateral, including signa

