&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;SQL Queries&lt;/strong&gt; team is responsible for the core of CockroachDB’s query execution and optimization layer. This group designs and delivers features that make our distributed SQL engine fast, reliable, and flexible for a wide range of workloads.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AI is transforming how we search, learn, and build, and databases are evolving to keep up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re forming a new &lt;strong&gt;Specialized Indexing&lt;/strong&gt; subteam within SQL Queries to expand CockroachDB’s indexing capabilities beyond traditional relational workloads. This team will design and implement high-performance indexing systems such as &lt;strong&gt;vector, full-text, and geospatial indexes&lt;/strong&gt; to support the next generation of &lt;strong&gt;AI-native and search-driven applications&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of this team, you’ll work on deep systems problems, collaborate across the SQL organization, and build production-quality features that make CockroachDB a unified platform for both structured and unstructured data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You Will&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and maintain specialized indexing features for CockroachDB, including &lt;strong&gt;vector&lt;/strong&gt;, full-text, and geospatial indexing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve the performance and reliability of existing vector indexing systems, including backfill, query planning, and import workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with other database teams to integrate new indexing mechanisms into the query engine.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop hybrid search capabilities that combine vector similarity and text-based search for modern AI and search workloads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in design discussions, code reviews, and release planning within the SQL organization.&lt;/li&gt;
